title: Farm value per liter of maple syrup in Ontario 2000 to 2018
yAxis: Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars. In total the number of data points it has is 19.
Overall Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars has increased over the Year.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2015 and 2016.
The highest Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars, of value 15.59 was reached at Year 2015
Minimum Farm value per liter in Canadian dollars about 10.5 was reached at Year 2000
